Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff; pink core; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Andronikos. Trimmed. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 050.10.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1098)
